Hi. We are having a very big project. we will build a roman house using a very special technology of the primitive people roman. In this video we start building roman bricks to initially implement the project. In the next video we will give you new surprises. Subscribe to follow the latest videos. Thank you

Primitive Technology Looking For Food. This is our latest video. This video we guide you to find food in the forest stream. By primitive survival skill we originally went to catch Pila conica which is a very nutritious shellfish. Then we went to find spices. We washed them all and cooked them with the pot that we had done before, then we added salt. Salt is a wonderful spice that we have created from seawater. We have made a very delicious dish. We will continue to make the latest videos on primitive technology and survival skills. Subscribe to a channel to watch the latest videos.

Hi. Building a Metal Furnace Copper (Cu) is our next video. In this video we have successfully separated copper from ore by furnace, we have improved the air injection system for the furnace. We were looking for copper ore in the stream. Copper Copper (CU) a great turning point in history. It changed the primordial to a new evolution of humanity. The bronze age is quite long and very developed, as a precondition for the iron age (Fe). The melting point of the copper metal is quite fast at 1000 degrees. We will continue to create many weak Copper metal pure enough to melt, creating copper metal tools. Then we will advance to the Iron Age (Fe). This is our fourth video of the primitive technology. In this video we created a bamboo water tank. When people do not have modern technology, primitive technology is a way for people to exist. These are original inventions. The bamboo water tank is a primitive technology that helps us keep water. We use the stone ax to cut bamboo, use bark to wire, we tighten the bamboo tube by the primitive technology. That is very difficult. We had to go deep into the forest to perform primitive skill. We did at a stream in the forest. I'm sure it's a good primitive technology video. We will continue to make videos of survival skills, the next primitive technology.

We go to the forest looking for resin, resin can waterproof very well. The plastic has a low melting point and hardens at normal temperature. Pine can kill some types of bacteria as well as do not cause toxicity at normal temperatures. We will perform a clean water filter in the following video. Primitive Technology with Survival Skills looking for food is our next video. In this video we go to the mangrove forest to look for food. Initially we caught some small crabs and shrimp. By the primitive technology we trapped to trap large crabs with shrimp. We dig a hole to trap the crabs, when the crabs fall they can not crawl. We caught two crabs and a large number of shrimp. We have boiled crab and grilled shrimp to eat. We picked a forest for cooking with crabs. We will continue to make the next video on primitive technology and survival skills. Primitive Technology Salt Water Filter is a full video tutorial on how to survive on an island where there is no fresh water. First we built a primitive pot, we perforated a small hole on the pot. Then we took a bamboo tube and made a chiller. Cooling water so that water vapor can condense into droplets to obtain maximum water. We take the sea water to boil. Fresh water then evaporates and produces fresh water. Salt will precipitate at the bottom of the pot. By the original technology we had to salvage sea water to obtain fresh water and salt. We will continue to work on the next video on primitive technology and survival skills. Subscribe to the channel to keep track of the latest videos
